I’m going to wear whatever I want whenever I want, even if it makes people uncomfortable. I’ve wasted too many precious moments of my life worrying about how my body appears to others. Is my outfit too sexy? Not sexy enough? Was this outfit meant for my body type? These are the thoughts I no longer allow to dictate what I wear. I choose to wear what makes me feel beautiful and confident and I refuse to apologize for it. 👏🏼

To be honest, I almost let these comments make me feel ashamed of my body. I even went back to the website I ordered this dress from to confirm that it was meant to be worn without a shirt underneath because I was nervous I had styled it wrong. Why else would there be such an uproar over it? Turns out I styled it exactly the way the designer intended for it to be worn. Swipe to see it on the website.😆

I hope you step into your power this week and have the courage to be 100% you. People will always stare so make it worth their while.❤️ Linking this dress in my stories in case anyone wants to piss people off with me.😘

Today marks the end of my first dog rescuing adventure.🐶 If you follow along in my stories then you know I decided to help my neighbor re-home his two dogs after he told me he was going to call animal control to pick up his pets.😢 The RGV has a major pet homelessness crisis and thousands of animals are put to death each year because they don’t have homes. I couldn’t bear the thought of these dogs being put to death so I posted on my IG story asking for help. Thanks to @diandra_villa and @_42wallabywaysydney we were able to get both dogs to better homes outside of the RGV.🙏🏼

We MUST do better for animals in the RGV. I’m sure it’s tempting to buy certain dog breeds from animal breeders such as Frenchies, Labradoodles, Pomeranians, etc. but it’s just NOT worth it. There are literally thousands of animals that need loving homes. By supporting animal breeding instead of adopting, we deny these animals the chance of a better life. Please consider adopting a puppy or kitten from your local shelter instead of buying. 🙌🏼

Equally as important is having your pets spayed and neutered to decrease overpopulation of homeless animals. Being a responsible pet owner includes making sure your pet does not contribute to overpopulation and suffering of animals.🥲 By following these simple steps we can make our community a more loving place for animals. Let’s all do our part to make our pets as happy as they make us.❤️

✨MAKING HISTORY✨

I’m still in disbelief that I was chosen to receive an award for making history in the RGV.🥹 Thank you to @hwntrgv for this incredible honor. 

As I said in my speech, this recognition also comes with great responsibility. Responsibility to continue showing up even when it’s hard, to continue breaking the mold of what lawyers should look like, act like, and dress like.👏🏼 If I had listened to every negative person who told me I would never make it on my own, then I wouldn’t be here today receiving an award for making history in the legal profession. 🙌🏼 As Latinas, we have come a long way, but there is still work to be done.💪🏼 May we all lift each other up, root for each other, and always be our authentic selves. We are stronger together. ❤️❤️❤️

In 2013 I lost my grandmother Raquel to breast cancer. Just one year later in 2014 I lost my aunt Laura to the same disease. This October, I encourage at-risk women to partake in life-saving breast imaging. 🙏🏼 

A few weeks ago I was referred by my doctor to get a mammogram due to my family history. A few days before my appointment, DHR called me to say they were canceling my appointment because my health insurance wasn’t going to cover the mammogram, but they mentioned I was eligible for a breast ultrasound. I was going to accept the fact that I couldn’t get a mammogram because I didn’t know private pay was an option. Thankfully, I talked to my amazing friend and owner of @openmriofmcallen, Sonia, and she encouraged me to call my doctor and request another referral for a mammogram without the assistance of health insurance. My doctor was happy to provide the second referral and within a few days I was at McAllen Breast Imaging (@openmriofmcallen) getting a mammogram! I loved my experience there!

Thankfully my breast ultrasound and mammogram  results came back normal and I tested negative for BRCA 1 and BRCA 2 gene mutations. 🙌🏼 I’m so glad I had a friend who encouraged me to be an advocate for my own health. I want to encourage all women to be your own biggest health advocate and always seek second opinions on decisions that could affect your health. ❤️

In honor of Breast Cancer Awareness month, I’m giving away 10 free mammograms to women who are uninsured or feel they are at risk for breast cancer. All you have to do is tag 1 friend in the comments. I’ll announce the winners on Friday October 13th. 🫶🏼 Please also share this reel with anyone you feel needs to see it! Awareness and education is key for early detection!❤️

Giveaway details: 
1. Imaging center will be @openmriofmcallen 
2. Women over 40 do not require a doctor’s referral to get a mammogram. 
3. If chosen, you must provide the contact information of a doctor’s office to send your results to.

It’s been a while since I’ve done an introductory post so allow me to tell all 25,000 of you a little bit about me. 🥹 I’m a lawyer, wife, daughter, friend, fashion lover, trauma survivor, cat lover, and all around girly girl. 🎀 

I’ve experienced dark days in which I’ve felt that life wasn’t worth living and I’ve experienced such amazing days that I’ve felt like my heart could burst. I’ve realized that the journey is so much more enjoyable than the destination. I’ve learned that I’m not meant to be loved by everyone. I’ve learned to protect my energy at all costs. I’ve learned that the more I practice gratitude the better life gets. 👏🏼

I still make mistakes every day and I’ve learned to laugh and learn instead of dwelling on the past. I know that I will never stop evolving into the best version of myself and that the days of struggle will be beautiful in hindsight. I’ve experienced grief and hardship that shaped me into a more loving and empathetic person. I’ve learned that things are always working out for me. ✨ 

My goal as a content creator is to inspire and relate to women because I believe that we are all connected and powerful. 💪🏼 Some days I wake up excited and some days I wake up sad. I used to think my broad range of emotions was a curse but I’ve realized it makes me human and able to empathize with my family, friends, and clients. ♥️ 

I’m incredibly thankful for all 25,000+ of you who continue to support me, make me smile when I’m down, and make me feel like I’m part of an incredible community. I hope every day gets easier for you and that your journey continues to be full of surprises. I hope you realize your worth and that you deserve everything your heart desires. 🫶🏼 Thank you for inspiring me every day and giving me the motivation to keep going. I love you all!!! 🥰 -Leah
